ent uncovered dynamic-access call-site list in every prompt, retries `./gradlew test` failures inside a bounded per-class mini-loop by sending the failing output back to the agent, clears agent context after each class attempt sequence, treats the phase as successful once any dynamic-access call site becomes covered, enforces per-class prompt-attempt limits, and fails the generation if the dynamic-access report disappears mid-phase.\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:59:    else Dynamic-access guidance available\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:6:\\\"\\\"\\\"Workflow entry point for improving dynamic-access coverage on an existing library.\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:9:focuses solely on generating new tests to improve dynamic-access coverage.\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:113:        description=\\\"Improve dynamic-access coverage for an existing library version.\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:151:        help=\\\"Enable resumable large-library chunking for dynamic-access workflows.\\\",\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:48:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:63:| Output directory | Caller | Absolute staging root for this gate invocation. The caller picks a path namespaced per (library, class) for the dynamic-access caller, or per coordinate for non-class-scoped callers — same convention as [native-metadata-exploration.md §4](native-metadata-exploration.md#4-output). The gate writes JVM-agent metadata to `<output_dir>/agent`, merged trace metadata to `<output_dir>/trace`, an